.. because that‚Äôs what everyone keeps asking us about!

our family means everything to us.
and both of our parents have shown us how to show up for each other, how to walk together through the hard times & support and love each other through it all. with this in mind, Spencer decided to design the ring himself. behind his design, was a lot of thought, intention and meaning.

little backstory: Spence‚Äôs parents met while working up north, working on a gold claim in the Yukon. a long time ago Spencer‚Äôs dad, John, gave Spence a gold nugget that he had mined while on the gold claim with Spencer‚Äôs mother, Sue. Spence held onto this gold piece for almost 20 years! Spencer hand picked the diamond and had the gold from his dad melted into the gold band of the ring and chose to do a single cast, so that it would remain a one of a kind piece. there is a tiny detail on the band.. a little peak that points to the diamond.. if you couldn‚Äôt already tell our love for the üèî
I had no idea that he planned to do this. the ring is such an intricate, thoughtful piece that i‚Äôll wear and cherish everyday for the rest of my life.

OKAY GUYS. What do you think?!! I think he did pretty ALL RIGHT with this whole proposal thing. part two: the BIG surprise üéâ

THE BIG SURPRISE -  OMG. I am still so impressed that spencer and everyone else involved were able to pull this off without me knowing... here we go...

We continued running through the forest, in a panic because we only have one hour to catch all our food for the next few days üêüüêü üé£ (or so he had me convinced) we finally get to the fishing spot, spencer throws his line in the water and it‚Äôs all good. Suddenly we hear a helicopter, and then a second helicopter coming towards us.

and then I get SMOKED IN THE FACE with a fishing hook. I‚Äôm not even joking, I pulled the fishing hook out of my face, thinking WHAT in the ACTUAL. Spencer says he was distracted by the helicopters coming in ... and asked me if I seen the people in the helicopters because they were wearing masks???? In my head i‚Äôm thinking ‚ÄúCool. masks. you just got me with a fish hook but....‚Äù

I continued to ignore the people in the helicopters, bc it‚Äôs rude to stare (duh) but also because we had been there before and there were always fishermen and hikers being dropped off via helicopter at this location. So nothing out of the norm really.

Finally spencer said ‚Äúno you NEED to look at those people coming out of the helicopters.‚Äù

LOW AND FREAKING behold

I turned around to see our families and friends running out of the heli‚Äôs towards us üò≠üò≠üò≠üò≠ (with coolers & coolers of food, beer and drinks! 700lb to be precise! #storytime üìô This weekend Spence is on a big hiking trip with some of his best friends from out of town. it‚Äôs all he‚Äôs been talking about for months, i‚Äôm so glad he is finally taking the time to do this üß° 
We spoke on the phone just 5 minutes ago, he was telling me about his trip so far and he mentioned that they covered a lot of ground today... they had accidentally climbed the wrong mountain, so everyone is really tired, so they set up camp early. I asked him where he was, and he said he climbed up another mountain to the ridge so that he could get cell reception and call me. Living the lifestyle that we do this is a pretty normal thing for him to do/say. so I never really thought anything of it and he continued to tell me more about the days adventure, when he was done he told me he loved me and he hung up.

I was in the bathroom washing my face when it dawned on me. HE JUST CLIMBED ANOTHER MOUNTAIN TO CALL ME and tell me that he loves me. WHAT THE. who does that??? this guy. {üí°üí°this is how easy it is to take each other for granted or become complacent in a relationship **this is me kicking myself** lol but also allowing this to be a gentle reminder + learning opportunity} sometimes when you do things together so often that they become not mundane but like routine, acts of love don‚Äôt stand out as much, but when you look for them, HELLO there they are ü•∞

I thought i‚Äôd share this with you so that you too can wash your face, reflect on the ways that your family expresses their love so that you too can feel that love instantly hit you upside the head üß°‚úåüèæüí° #spencieboy #loveyou #complacencyisnotanoption #relationshiptalk

i don‚Äôt understand it. 
i‚Äôm sad. i‚Äôm angry. 
but it‚Äôs not enough. 
my biggest fear? to say the wrong thing. but to say nothing at all? worse. I am not a writer, I don‚Äôt have beautiful words all the time. I‚Äôve been processing, learning, unlearning too. it was out of my awareness that being a non racist isn‚Äôt enough. having black friends and family members, and loving them fully isn‚Äôt enough. it‚Äôs a start. but far from everything.

it‚Äôs still appalling that there is a need to rally for the importance of the LIVES (!!!?) of our brothers + sisters. (how could this be? i‚Äôve always seen them as my equals. but, seemingly what i think/want to believe is not always true) it‚Äôs time. time to lift them up üñ§ and it been a long freaking time coming. 
if words of racism slip from someone you know. stand up. bring the awareness. show them that is not the way. that racism in any way: direct, discrete, individual, systemic, deserves exactly zero space in this world. it is wrong. everyday. all the time. 
in closing, thank you @morganharpernichols for always having the words when I do not ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî ‚§µÔ∏è
‚ÄúEngage in the long, faithful work
of awakening
with your heart and mind open to the possibility
that things are more complex than they once seemed.

And as hard as it is to hold all of this,
you are still free to dream:
you do not have to be who you used to be.
You do not have to think the way you used to think.
You are free to take hopeful, thoughtful action
in pursuit of better things.

So here‚Äôs to new beginnings,
knowing it is impossible to ignore the long history,
opening up to the mystery
that grace still finds you here.

And grace is unmerited favor
but it might not always look the way you want it to.
It will invite you out in the open
and it will also reveal what has been broken.
You might have to unlearn the way you thought things would be.
You might find that being undone
is the best way to move on, humbly, mindfully, wholly.

For how liberating it is
to pursue wholeness over perfection,
finding that grace is more than a beautiful word,

I‚Äôll be honest it‚Äôs been a lot of different emotions around here. keeping routines and keeping my gratitude practice has helped. some days are high some are low. finding little joys in everyday: iced coffee + walks in the sunshine, sweatpants all day errrdayy üôåüèª but also getting ready + wearing lipsense helps me feel good & helps me be productive. local contactless drop offs have been my FAVOURITE thing. dropping happy mail on your doorsteps with treats and encouraging notes brings me so. much. joy üëèüèæüì¶ü•∞ receiving your messages and VIDEOS üò≠üòç about how fun it is to get mail right now, how much you love your new products + how good you feel bc now you have the time to take care of your skin and experiment with different products #thefeelgoodstuff üíå

i‚Äôve been keeping busy with lots of mini adventures + mini mountain trips. even if it‚Äôs just to pull over and breathe in the mountain air. there has been lots of time to feel. think. cry. smile. laugh. experience. and for that i‚Äôm grateful. I remember being so caught up in a work frienzie saying to myself ‚Äúyou don‚Äôt have time to think/worry/feel/talk about/dive into this.‚Äù so taking a breather and settling into feelings has been a good thing for me.

however, there have been days where my highest achievement was eating leftover stir fry for breakfast, falling asleep again and then getting the mail. {then learning later that there was chinese food in my hair. i‚Äôm a legit quarantine slob you guys} ü§£ it‚Äôs amazing how wound up can end up (without even really knowing) from ‚Äútoo much going on‚Äù and just not taking care of yourself.. and I think that just now.. 6 weeks into this whole thing, my mind/body/spirit is starting to relax, accept and fully sink into whatever this is.

but truly: whatever you are doing. you are doing it right. if your quarantine looks like laying on the couch all day, great. your body probably needs the rest. if you are doing all the online seminars, learning all the things, great. mental stimulation is probably what  y o u  need right now. maybe running 10km everyday is what you need. whatever it is, you‚Äôre also doing great. everybody needs different things right now and it‚Äôs all okay ü§ç

my best friend. this little guy snuggles + loves real hard. but let me tell you. he can be a little fire cracker. he has ptsd + he can‚Äôt just let things go. when he got hurt, it took away his innocence and left him feeling unprotected, insecure, full of mistrust. every time he is triggered (when he sees big dogs), he goes right back to those bad memories. his body takes the same position. he makes the same high pitched, terrified sounds. his defence mechanism is to be the first to ‚Äúthrow a punch.‚Äù and when he is triggered, it takes hours to calm him back down.

dang. does it ever sound/feel familiar. sometimes i joke about how arlo thinks he is human. sometimes he sits like a human and makes demands like a human üòÇ but when i really think about it, his emotions seem even more human than ever. his ptsd limits him from being involved in many things. his anxiety means that he doesn‚Äôt get to play like most dogs do. he misses out, on a lot. it makes me sad. it‚Äôs hard to manage sometimes. but despite all of it, i wouldn‚Äôt trade him for any other dog. he got me out of bed when I was at my worst. helped me take little steps everyday to manage my depression/anxiety. like get out of bed, go for a walk, be outside, talk to other people and engage in play.

i‚Äôve heard many times ‚Äúoh it must be hard sometimes to have a reactive dog‚Äù & yes it is. but also it‚Äôs not. we‚Äôre the same. it‚Äòs just life as we know it. we do take extra safety precautions. muzzle, extra + specific training classes, no dog parks, no play dates, very cautious social interactions with long slow introductions. but every single day i wake up to this face + start my day with a smile on my face because of him. and i just wish that I could give some of my years to keep him with me longer ü•∞üêæ but also, people. plz keep your dogs on a leash so i can walk my dog without having a damn heart attack every time i go outside. k thanks üòÇ
